Node JS Tutorial for Beginners #6 - Modules and require()

What is a module?
A simple or complex funcionality organized in single or multiple js files which can be reused. 
(a JS file)

What does the word ‘require’ do?
Includes external modules that exist in seperate files. 

How do we bring another module into the file the we are working in?
require(./'')

What do we have to do to make a module available?
module.exports and set it equal to whatever function you plan on using. 

